+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BoE1kyQAncLx6kMerfCMXr","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have everything. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## Codebase Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the entire codebase. Here's the complete analysis:\n\n---\n\n### 1. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── types.ts          (Core type definitions)\n│   │   ├── engine.ts         (Build engine implementation)\n│   │   ├── templates.ts      (Template implementations)\n│   │   └── index.ts          (Exports)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       └── .gitkeep          (Empty - plugins to be implemented)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts          (Core engine tests)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n│       ├── dev-server.test.ts\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n│       ├── rss-feed.test.ts\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts\n│       ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n│       └── taxonomy.test.ts\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n└── .eslintrc.cjs\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. PLUGIN INTERFACE (src/core/types.ts) - COMPLETE\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Plugin Fields:**\n- `name`: Plugin identifier string\n- `version`: Semantic version string\n- `dependencies`: Array of plugin names this depends on (for DAG resolution)\n- `hooks`: Object containing 3 optional hooks\n\n**Hook Signature:**\n- `beforeBuild`: Runs before any transformations (can be async)\n- `transformContent`: Transforms each file in sequence (can be async), applied once per file per plugin\n- `afterBuild`: Runs after all files processed (can be async)\n\n---\n\n### 3. BUILD ENGINE (src/core/engine.ts) - COMPLETE\n\n```typescript\nexport class BuildEngine {\n  private plugins: Plugin[] = [];\n  private templates: Map<string, Template> = new Map();\n\n  constructor(private config: SiteConfig) {}\n\n  registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin): void\n  registerTemplate(template: Template): void\n  \n  resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]\n    // Topological sort using DFS\n    // Throws on circular dependencies\n    // Throws on missing dependencies\n  \n  async build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>\n    // 1. Creates context with config, files, empty output/assets/data maps\n    // 2. Resolves plugin execution order\n    // 3. Calls beforeBuild hooks in order\n    // 4. Calls transformContent hooks on each file in order\n    // 5. Renders templates for each file\n    // 6. Calls afterBuild hooks in order\n    // 7. Returns populated context\n  \n  getPlugins(): Plugin[]\n  getTemplates(): Map<string, Template>\n}\n```\n\n**Build Flow:**\n1. **Plugin Order Resolution**: Uses topological sort (DFS) to ensure dependencies execute first\n2. **beforeBuild Phase**: All plugins' beforeBuild hooks run (can write to ctx.data)\n3. **transformContent Phase**: For each file, each plugin's transformContent hook transforms it in sequence\n4. **Template Rendering**: Default template or specified template renders each file to HTML\n5. **afterBuild Phase**: All plugins' afterBuild hooks run (can read from ctx.files and ctx.data)\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- Plugins with dependencies must have their dependencies registered as plugins\n- Circular dependencies detected and throw error\n- Missing dependencies detected and throw error\n- Template data includes: title, slug, date, tags, metadata fields, siteTitle, baseUrl\n\n---\n\n### 4. TEMPLATE SYSTEM (src/core/templates.ts) - COMPLETE\n\n```typescript\nexport function createDefaultTemplate(): Template\n  // Returns template named 'default'\n  // Renders: <!DOCTYPE html> with <head> metadata and <body> with article\n  // Shows: title, date (if present), content\n\nexport function createListTemplate(): Template\n  // Returns template named 'list'\n  // Renders: <!DOCTYPE html> with <head> metadata and <body> with div.list\n  // Shows: title, content\n```\n\n**Template Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\nThe render function receives:\n- `content`: The file's content (HTML string)\n- `data`: Object with title, slug, date, tags, metadata, siteTitle, baseUrl\n\n---\n\n### 5. CORE TESTS (tests/core.test.ts) - 15 TEST CASES\n\n| Test | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `registers plugins` | Plugin.registerPlugin adds to engine |\n| `registers templates` | Template.registerTemplate adds to engine |\n| `builds with default template and renders HTML` | Render uses default template with content |\n| `builds with list template and renders list HTML` | Render uses list template when specified |\n| `outputs raw content when no matching template` | Falls back t