+# SSG Toolkit Plugins Implementation Plan
+
+> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.
+
+**Goal:** Implement 8 plugins for the SSG toolkit, satisfying all 60 plugin tests plus maintaining 15 existing core tests.
+
+**Architecture:** Each plugin is a standalone TypeScript file in `src/plugins/` that exports a `createXxxPlugin()` factory function returning a `Plugin` object. Plugins communicate via the shared `ctx.data` Map and `ctx.output` Map. Three waves of dependencies: Wave 1 (no deps), Wave 2 (depends on Wave 1), Wave 3 (depends on Wave 2).
+
+**Tech Stack:** TypeScript (strict, ES2022, Node16 modules), marked v17 for markdown, vitest for testing.
+
+---
+
+## Wave 1 — No Dependencies
+
+### Task 1: markdown-ext plugin
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/plugins/markdown-ext.ts`
+- Test: `tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts` (existing, 8 tests)
+
+**Implementation:**
+
+Uses `marked` library for basic markdown→HTML. Custom preprocessing for:
+1. Footnotes: `[^N]` inline refs → `<sup><a href="#fn-N">N</a></sup>`, `[^N]: text` defs → collected into `<section class="footnotes"><ol><li id="fn-N">text</li></ol></section>` appended at end
+2. Admonition containers: `:::type\ncontent\n:::` → `<div class="admonition admonition-type">\n<p>content</p>\n</div>`
+
+Key points:
+- Process footnotes and containers BEFORE passing to marked
+- Footnote defs removed from content, refs replaced with `<sup>` HTML
+- Admonition blocks converted to HTML divs before markdown pass
+- Return new ContentFile with transformed content
+
+### Task 2: asset-pipeline plugin
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/plugins/asset-pipeline.ts`
+- Test: `tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts` (existing, 8 tests)
+
+**Implementation:**
+
+`transformContent` hook that:
+1. Uses regex to find `src="./filename"` and `href="./filename"` patterns
+2. Rewrites to `src="/assets/filename"` and `href="/assets/filename"`
+3. Collects discovered filenames into `ctx.data['asset-manifest'] = { assets: string[] }`
+4. Skips absolute URLs (https://) and already-rewritten `/assets/` URLs
+5. Accumulates assets across multiple files (initialize manifest if not exists)
+
+### Task 3: syntax-highlight plugin
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/plugins/syntax-highlight.ts`
+- Test: `tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts` (existing, 8 tests)
+
+**Implementation:**
+
+`transformContent` hook that:
+1. Regex matches `<pre><code class="language-(\w+)">` patterns
+2. Adds `highlighted` to the class: `class="language-X highlighted"`
+3. Adds `data-language="X"` to the `<pre>` tag
+4. Does NOT modify `<pre><code>` without language class
+5. Does NOT modify inline `<code>` (only `<pre><code>` blocks)
+
+### Task 4: taxonomy plugin
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/plugins/taxonomy.ts`
+- Test: `tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts` (existing, 8 tests)
+
+**Implementation:**
+
+`beforeBuild` hook:
+1. Iterate `ctx.files`, collect tags (case-normalized to lowercase)
+2. Build `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` mapping tag → files
+3. Store in `ctx.data.set('taxonomy-tags', tagMap)`
+
+`afterBuild` hook:
+1. Read tagMap from `ctx.data`
+2. For each tag, generate `tags/{tag}.html` page listing all file titles
+3. Store in `ctx.output`
+
+---
+
+## Wave 2 — Depend on Wave 1
+
+### Task 5: rss-feed plugin
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/plugins/rss-feed.ts`
+- Test: `tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts` (existing, 8 tests)
+
+**Dependencies:** `['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy']`
+
+**Implementation:**
+
+`afterBuild` hook:
+1. Sort files by date descending (newest first), files without dates go last
+2. Build RSS 2.0 XML with channel info from config
+3. Each file → `<item>` with `<title>`, `<link>` (baseUrl/slug.html), `<description>` with CDATA-wrapped content
+4. If file has tags AND taxonomy-tags exists in ctx.data, add `<category>` elements
+5. If file has date, add `<pubDate>` (skip if undefined)
+6. Store in `ctx.output.set('feed.xml', xml)`
+
+### Task 6: search-index plugin
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/plugins/search-index.ts`
+- Test: `tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts` (existing, 7 tests)
+
+**Dependencies:** `['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight']`
+
+**Implementation:**
+
+`afterBuild` hook:
+1. Map each file to `{ slug, title, content (HTML-stripped), tags? }`
+2. Strip HTML: remove all `<...>` tags, keep text content
+3. Include code block text (it's already in the content after stripping tags)
+4. Include tags array if file has tags
+5. JSON.stringify the array, store in `ctx.output.set('search-index.json', json)`
+
+---
+
+## Wave 3 — Depend on Wave 2
+
+### Task 7: sitemap plugin
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/plugins/sitemap.ts`
+- Test: `tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts` (existing, 7 tests)
+
+**Dependencies:** `['taxonomy', 'rss-feed']`
+
+**Implementation:**
+
+`afterBuild` hook:
+1. Collect all keys from `ctx.output` (excluding `sitemap.xml` itself)
+2. Build XML sitemap with `<?xml>` declaration, `<urlset>` wrapper
+3. Each output key → `<url><loc>baseUrl/key</loc></url>`
+4. Store in `ctx.output.set('sitemap.xml', xml)`
+
+### Task 8: dev-server plugin
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/plugins/dev-server.ts`
+- Test: `tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts` (existing, 7 tests)
+
+**Dependencies:** `['asset-pipeline', 'search-index']`
+
+**Implementation:**
+
+`afterBuild` hook:
+1. Read `asset-manifest` from ctx.data (or default to `{ assets: [] }`)
+2. Build routes array:
+   - Asset routes: each asset → `{ path: '/assets/' + asset, handler: 'asset' }`
+   - Content routes: each .html key in ctx.output → `{ path: '/' + key, handler: 'static' }`
+3. Determine searchIndexPath: '/search-index.json' if exists in output, else ''
+4. Config: `{ port: 3000, routes, assetPaths: manifest.assets, searchIndexPath }`
+5. Store in `ctx.data.set('dev-server-config', config)`
+
+---
+
+## Validation
+
+Run after all plugins implemented:
+- `npm test` — all 75 tests pass
+- `npm run build` — TypeScript compiles
+- `npm run lint` — ESLint clean
